text: Gymnocarpos kuriensis is a species of plant in the family Caryophyllaceae. It is endemic to Yemen. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical dry forests, subtropical or tropical dry shrubland, and rocky areas. ==References== Category:Endemic flora of Socotra Category:Caryophyllaceae Category:Vulnerable plants Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot
